                            <comment id="324693" author="adilger" created="Tue, 1 Feb 2022 08:35:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think all of the failures with disk2_10-ldiskfs and disk2_12-ldiskfs are because these images have 2 MDTs and/or 2 OSTs.  All of the passing cases are with 1 MDT/1 OST (ldiskfs and zfs).  For some reason I don&apos;t see results for disk2_5-ldiskfs, but not sure why.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="324682" author="adilger" created="Tue, 1 Feb 2022 07:26:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;init.d&lt;/tt&gt; directory is a &quot;remote&quot; directory It looks like the problem &lt;b&gt;might&lt;/b&gt; be that the &lt;tt&gt;mdt2&lt;/tt&gt; image is not being mounted when test_32b run itself is using MDSCOUNT=1?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
